The paper deals with developing classical algorithms for matrix transformations that are defined via the singular value decomposition of the matrix. This involves techniques from linear algebra, optimization, and numerical analysis, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also mentions the use of low-rank approximations, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis, covered in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, covered in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
